<style type="text/css" media="print" >
/* Default Print Stylesheet Template
by Rob Glazebrook of CSSnewbie.com
Last Updated: June 4, 2008
Feel free (nay, compelled) to edit, append, and
manipulate this file as you see fit. */
/* SECTION 1: Set default width, margin, float, and
background. This prevents elements from extending
beyond the edge of the printed page, and prevents
unnecessary background images from printing */
* {
-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;
}
body {
font-size: 18pt;
width: auto;
height: auto;
border: 0;
padding: 0;
float: none !important;
overflow: visible;
}
html {
width: 100%;
height: 100%;
overflow: visible;
}
@page {
size: letter landscape;
margin: 0;
}
/* SECTION 2: Remove any elements not needed in print.
This would include navigation, ads, sidebars, etc. */
.nestedarrow,
.controls,
.reveal .progress,
.reveal.overview,
.fork-reveal,
.share-reveal,
.state-background {
display: none !important;
}
/* SECTION 3: Set body font face, size, and color.
Consider using a serif font for readability. */
body, p, td, li, div {
font-size: 18pt;
}
/* SECTION 4: Set heading font face, sizes, and color.
Diffrentiate your headings from your body text.
Perhaps use a large sans-serif for distinction. */
h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6 {
text-shadow: 0 0 0 #000 !important;
}
/* SECTION 5: Make hyperlinks more usable.
Ensure links are underlined, and consider appending
the URL to the end of the link for usability. */
a:link,
a:visited {
font-weight: bold;
text-decoration: underline;
}
/* SECTION 6: more reveal.js specific additions by @skypanther */
ul, ol, div, p {
visibility: visible;
position: static;
width: auto;
height: auto;
display: block;
overflow: visible;
margin: auto;
}

position: static;

alt="The Roslin Institute"/></p>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>R future</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<p>Future is an R package by <a href="https://twitter.com/henrikbengtsson">Henrik Bengtsson</a>, available on <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/package=future">CRAN</a>.</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; install.packages(&quot;future&quot;)
&gt; library(future)
&gt; plan(multiprocess) # more on that later
</code></pre>
<p>It introduces yet another assignment operator: <code>%&lt;-%</code></p>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>`%&lt;-%` is yet another assignment operator:</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<pre><code class="r">&gt; a %&lt;-% 42
&gt; a
[1] 42
&gt; b %&lt;-% c(rep(a, 4), 43)
&gt; b
[1] 42 42 42 42 43
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>`%&lt;-%` is non blocking (1&#x2F;2):</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<p>First, let&#39;s create slow functions:</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; slow &lt;- function(myFunc, by_seconds = 3) {
+ return(
+ function(...) {
+ Sys.sleep(by_seconds)
+ myFunc(...)
+ }
+ )
+ }
&gt;
&gt; slow_rnorm &lt;- slow(rnorm)
&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt;
&gt; slow_rnorm(4)
[1] -0.696 -0.730 0.704 -1.719
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 3.01 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>`%&lt;-%` is non blocking (2&#x2F;2):</h3>
<div class="column column1 slideContent" >
<p>Without <code>%&lt;-%</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt; a &lt;- slow_rnorm(2)
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 3.01 secs
&gt;
&gt; a
[1] -0.2310 0.0694
</code></pre>
</div>
<div class="column column2 slideContent" >
<p>With <code>%&lt;-%</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt; b %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(2)
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 0.011 secs
&gt;
&gt; b
[1] 0.109 0.153
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>`%&lt;-%` is **not** magic:</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<p>It create a <em>future</em>, a variable that will be available in the future.
The task is <strong>not</strong> magically optimised, it runs in the background.
When the variable is needed, the R (main) process will wait until the <em>future</em> is resolved.</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt; b %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(2)
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 0.00704 secs
&gt;
&gt; b
[1] 0.172 1.245
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 3.02 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>*futures* can be run in parallel:</h3>
<div class="column column1 slideContent" >
<p>Standard assignment:</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt; x1 &lt;- slow_rnorm(2)
&gt; x2 &lt;- slow_rnorm(2)
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 6.01 secs
&gt;
&gt; list(x1, x2)
[[1]]
[1] -0.651 -0.693
[[2]]
[1] -1.41 -1.08
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 6.02 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
<div class="column column2 slideContent" >
<p>Assignment with future:</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt; x3 %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(2)
&gt; x4 %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(2)
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 0.0482 secs
&gt;
&gt; list(x3, x4)
[[1]]
[1] 0.731 -2.045
[[2]]
[1] 0.3504 0.0184
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 3.06 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>*future* allows easy parallelisation of heterogeneous tasks (1&#x2F;3)</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<pre><code class="r">&gt; myMat &lt;- matrix(1:6, ncol = 2)
&gt; slow_apply &lt;- slow(apply)
</code></pre>
<p>Standard assignment:</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt; myMean &lt;- slow_apply(myMat, 1, mean)
&gt; mySd &lt;- slow_apply(myMat, 1, sd)
&gt; myRnorm &lt;- slow_rnorm(3)
&gt; myRunif &lt;- slow(runif)(3)
&gt;
&gt; data.frame(myMean, mySd, myRnorm, myRunif)
myMean mySd myRnorm myRunif
1 2.5 2.12 -1.451 0.809
2 3.5 2.12 -1.592 0.972
3 4.5 2.12 0.943 0.660
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 12 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>*future* allows easy parallelisation of heterogenous tasks (2&#x2F;3)</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<p>Parallelization with <em>future</em>:</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt; myMean %&lt;-% slow_apply(myMat, 1, mean)
&gt; mySd %&lt;-% slow_apply(myMat, 1, sd)
&gt; myRnorm %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(3)
&gt; myRunif %&lt;-% slow(runif)(3)
&gt;
&gt; data.frame(myMean, mySd, myRnorm, myRunif)
myMean mySd myRnorm myRunif
1 2.5 2.12 0.504 0.898
2 3.5 2.12 -1.134 0.228
3 4.5 2.12 -0.219 0.491
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 3.11 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>*future* allows easy parallelisation of heterogenous tasks (3&#x2F;3)</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<p>Parallelization with parallel:</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; library(parallel)
&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt; myCommands &lt;- c(
+ myMean = &quot;slow_apply(myMat, 1, mean)&quot;,
+ mySd = &quot;slow_apply(myMat, 1, sd)&quot;,
+ myRnorm = &quot;slow_rnorm(3)&quot;,
+ myRunif = &quot;slow(runif)(3)&quot;
+ )
&gt;
&gt; as.data.frame(mclapply( # not parallel on windows, but should work elsewhere
+ myCommands,
+ function(x) eval(parse(text = x))
+ # mc.cores = 4L &lt;- add this on non windows OS
+ ))
myMean mySd myRnorm myRunif
1 2.5 2.12 -0.241 0.651
2 3.5 2.12 -0.445 0.522
3 4.5 2.12 1.879 0.199
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 12 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>A *future_mclapply* draft function (1&#x2F;3)</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<pre><code class="r">&gt; future_mclapply &lt;- function(myList, myFunction) {
+ if(is.vector(myList)) myList &lt;- as.list(myList) # the function will work on vectors to
+ for(i in seq_along(myList)) {
+ command &lt;- paste0(
+ &quot;x&quot;,
+ i,
+ &quot; %&lt;-% do.call(&quot;,
+ deparse(substitute(myFunction)),
+ &quot;,&quot;,
+ deparse(substitute(myList[i])),
+ &quot;)&quot;
+ )
+ eval(parse(text = command))
+ }
+ outputVars &lt;- paste(
+ paste0(&quot;x&quot;, seq_along(myList)),
+ collapse = &quot;, &quot;
+ )
+ output &lt;- eval(parse(text = paste0(&quot;list(&quot;, outputVars, &quot;)&quot;)))
+ names(output) &lt;- names(myList)
+ return(output)
+ }
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>A *future_mclapply* draft function (2&#x2F;3)</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<pre><code class="r">&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt;
&gt; future_mclapply(
+ list(1:5, 6:10, pi),
+ slow(mean)
+ )
[[1]]
[1] 3
[[2]]
[1] 8
[[3]]
[1] 3.14
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 3.04 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>A *future_mclapply* function (3&#x2F;3)</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<p>Or the hidden function (may change / disappear in future version of the package):</p>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt;
&gt; future:::flapply(
+ list(1:5, 6:10, pi),
+ slow(mean)
+ )
[[1]]
[1] 3
[[2]]
[1] 8
[[3]]
[1] 3.14
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 3.03 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>One package, many plans</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<ul>
<li><code>plan(multiprocess)</code>: parallel, non blocking</li>
<li><code>plan(eager)</code>: non parallel, blocking (default)</li>
<li><code>plan(lazy)</code>: non parallel, non blocking</li>
<li><code>plan(cluster, workers = c(&quot;n1&quot;, &quot;n2&quot;, &quot;n3&quot;))</code>: run in a cluster, non blocking. Nice gestion of the global variables.</li>
<li>see also <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/future.BatchJobs/index.html">future.BatchJobs</a> for more cluster plans.</li>
</ul>
<p>Write package using <em>future</em>, users will choose how to run it by changing the <code>plan</code>.</p>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>Limiting the number of cores in `plan(multiprocess)` (1&#x2F;2)</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<pre><code class="r">&gt; availableCores()
system
8
&gt;
&gt; plan(multiprocess(workers = 1 + 3)) # 1 main + 3 background
&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt; x1 %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(1)
&gt; x2 %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(1)
&gt; x3 %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(1)
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 0.718 secs
&gt;
&gt; c(x1, x2, x3)
[1] -0.323 -1.327 -1.274
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 3.73 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>Limiting the number of cores in `plan(multiprocess)` (2&#x2F;2)</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<pre><code class="r">&gt; plan(multiprocess(workers = 1 + 2)) # 1 main + 2 background
&gt; t0 &lt;- Sys.time()
&gt; x1 %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(1)
&gt; x2 %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(1)
&gt; x3 %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(1) # no more background process available, blocks the main process
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 3.51 secs
&gt;
&gt; c(x1, x2, x3)
[1] -0.266 0.679 0.206
&gt;
&gt; Sys.time() - t0
Time difference of 6.52 secs
</code></pre>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>Miscellaneous</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<ul>
<li>Nested features are supported, see this <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/future/vignettes/future-3-topologies.html">vignette</a></li>
<li>Check if a future is resolved:</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="r">&gt; x1 %&lt;-% slow_rnorm(3)
&gt; f &lt;- futureOf(x1)
&gt; resolved(f)
[1] FALSE
</code></pre>
<ul>
<li>No easy way to stop an unresolved future at the moment (killing the process?)</li>
</ul>
</div>
</section>
<section data-transition="linear" data-transition-speed="default">
<h3>Links</h3>
<div class="slideContent" >
<ul>
<li>The package: <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/future/index.html">(https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/future/index.html)</a></li>
<li>The comprehensive vignette:<a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/future/vignettes/future-1-overview.html">https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/future/vignettes/future-1-overview.html</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.jottr.org/2016/07/a-future-for-r-slides-from-user-2016.html">slides from useR2016</a> by Henrik Bengtsson.</li>
<li><a href="https://cran.r-project.org/package=doFuture"><code>doFuture</code> package</a>: alternative to <code>doMC</code>, <code>doParallel</code>, <code>doMPI</code>, and <code>doSNOW</code>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</section>

}
